com.gemalto.idp.mobile.authentication.mode.face

Interface FaceAuthEnrollerCallback


  • public interface FaceAuthEnrollerCallback
    Face Auth Mode enrollment completed (either success or failure) handler. One of the method is always called so that the UI code does not have to implement any timeout upon it.
    Since:
    4.2

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void onEnrollError(IdpException e)
      This callback function is called if there is other error occurs during enrollment.
      void onEnrollFinish(FaceAuthStatus status)
      It is called as soon as the enrollment process completes.

    • Method Detail

      • onEnrollFinish

        void onEnrollFinish(FaceAuthStatus status)
        It is called as soon as the enrollment process completes.

        It is guaranteed that:

        • This method is called on the main UI thread, so that the UI code can directly act on it.
        • This method is never called from within the context of the enroller method - i.e. always after the enroll method returns.
        Application should check for the status for the result of the enrollment. on EnrollFinish does not guarantee the success of enrollment.
        Parameters:
        status - The status of the enrollment process

      • onEnrollError

        void onEnrollError(IdpException e)
        This callback function is called if there is other error occurs during enrollment. eg: password manager is not logged in, device support, OS support or other operations related to the SDK.
        Parameters:
        e - exception object indicating problem during enrollment process.
